	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f109636687686183>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=5935&mid=109636687686183>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=5935&mid=109636687686183>Wow, they do glow!</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=5935&mid=109636687686183#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Sep 28th 6:21 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=99844><span id=Sage>Tadwenai</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>117 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have killed about 30 Wurms indiscriminately in an attempt to get my 3 glowing worm bile.&nbsp;&nbsp;On my first (north of tunnel) and second (South west of tunnel) success getting a &quot;Glowing Worm Bile&quot; I did not notice any glow. Of course they were both day kills and I probably could not have seen the glow anyway.   On my last success I did notice, though it did not strike me until after the kill, that the worm would occasionally illuminate the walls of the cave as it walked toward me although it was not constant.  It appeared much like the glow I myself cast on the ice at night as I cross the Great Divide with my Ranger. <br><br>So it is true, but anyway you slice it you still have to kill lots of worms to get the &quot;little glow worms&quot; to pop.  If you sit around waiting for the glimmering glow worms to slither by then you will NOT have the glow of success beaming from your frost covered face!  <br><br><br>P.S.  Why is it not wUrm bile instead of wOrm bile?<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Sep 28 06:27:37 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Tadwenai <br>Half Elf <br>Pathfinder<br>Xegony<br><br>Master Baker (198), Master Brewer (248 - Trophy), Master Bait'er? (189), Master Begger (174), Master Fletcher (136), Master Smith (162), Master Tailor (142), Master Drunk (200), Master Potter (148)</td></tr>
