	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=5935&mid=10811926881533>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=5935&mid=10811926881533>Spawns, Cash, and Biles</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=5935&mid=10811926881533#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Apr 5th 3:20 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=186015><span id=Guru>Athairic Defender of Justice</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>35 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.65]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>While I understand and respect the sentiment of those giving instruction on looking for the &quot;glowing wurms&quot; to get the biles, I have found that spending some time (perhaps and hour or two) doing a slaughter fest will yield at least one or two biles.<br><br>I focus only on the young wurms in the area south of the wurm caves (approx. pos100, neg6500) as well as any wandering ancients or elder that head south out of the caves.<br><br>I part my pet, race to spawn points, have the pet attack and put myself far enough back not to draw aggro.&nbsp;&nbsp;At levels 50+, the pet can easily handle the young wurms while I spend time finding the next victim.<br><br>The payoff while waiting for the glowing worm biles is not that bad.  Most wurms drop about 3pp per kill, and the ancients will often drop a scaled tunic or a level 44+ spell.  No, you won't get rich, but you will have a nice chunk of change.<br><br>It is imperative that you keep the killing up in order to spawn the worms with the bile.  From my count, I killed 252 wurms in order to get 7 biles (I kept a few to soften the frustration if I fail on a combine).<br><br>If you are persistent, the rewards are there.<br><br>Good luck to you all.<br></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Athairic of the Mooar Empire<br>Barbarian Shaman<br>57th Life Cycle<br>Lanys T'Vyl Server<br><br>I seek those who believe.</td></tr>
