	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Feb 9th 7:44 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=185424><span id= >Draiodoir</span></a><br><span id=notbold>4 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>When hunting for these biles, hunt at night (game time), and look for the shard wurms that glow.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you look at the ground around a shard wurm, you will see an aura of light surrounding a shard wurm that will drop a bile.  This was much more reliable for me than trying to tell the difference in whether the &quot;skin&quot; was glowing.  You can see the ones with the bile from a mile away.  Just watch them walk, and if the light around them moves with them, that's the one you want to kill.<br><br>If this post isn't clear, feel free to send me a tell (on Kane Bayle, or EQ Live) if you have any questions.<br><br>Draiodoir<br>Magician - 45th Season<br>Kane Bayle<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
